llapsing system or of a\ncosmological model. The analysis of energy conditions, considering an effective\nfluid shows that the term of the aether contributes significantly for the\naccelerated expansion of the system for the case in which the energy density is\nconstant. On the other hand, for the vacuum case ($\\rho_0=0$), the energy\nconditions are all satisfied for the aether fluid.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Jul 2018 17:52:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 9 Nov 2018 10:49:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 25 Mar 2019 17:01:55 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 12 Sep 2019 12:01:44 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 15 Nov 2019 19:27:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-11"}
