erned became known as the ``Extended Solar Cycle'' (ESC). The\npatterns of the ESC appeared to extend the wings of the activity butterfly back\nin time, nearly a decade before the formation of the sunspot pattern, and to\nmuch higher solar latitudes. In this short review, we describe their\nobservational patterns of the ESC and discuss possible connections to the solar\ndynamo as we depart on a multi-national collaboration to investigate the\norigins of solar magnetism through a blend of archived and contemporary data\nanalysis with the goal of improving solar dynamo understanding and modeling.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Jul 2018 18:42:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-23"}
